REVISED PROPOSAL

Based on my last proposal, I'd like to now focus on the character profiling aspect of the project. After a little more research into the topic I've read into the research of Dr Michal Kosinski whose findings certainly contributed to the work later conducted by Cambridge Analytica and their involvement with the US Presidential Elections, possibly Brexit and other political influence around the world.

The _myPersonality_ project was research carried out by Kosinski which 'was a Facebook App that allowed its users to participate in psychological research by filling in a personality questionnaire'. The data has officially been taken offline 'due to a lack of time to maintain it' but the raw data is still available. The dataset contains an encrypted user ID, a Facebook status and the results of the personality test recorded as weights based on the _Five Factor Model_ (and some other data). This data has been used before to train models to identify personality traits based on text given.

As the _myPersonality_ dataset is anonymous there is no age, gender and certainly no image attached. But as an initial area of exploration I'd like to to see if a model could be trained on the _myPersonality_ dataset to determine a personality type; then use this on Facebook profiles online, scraping text and a profile picture, to start to connect personality types to faces to create a new dataset; then (partly so as to avoid legal issues with using people faces which I am unaware of) use this second dataset to train a style-based GAN to create what it understands to be an agreeable face, or what it undersatnds an extrovert to look like.

As a visual output I am imagining reasonably simple digital portraits displayed on a monitor with a caption for each face explaining their character profile. If possible perhaps these could be interpolating between faces as they often are moving from someone who is conscientious to someone who is neurotic, but I can't be sure of that yet.

The first thing to do is to interrogate the _myPersonality_ dataset by training and playing with different models to see what kind of results I can get. If I feed it text like "I can't wait to try new things" would it return a personality score in-line with someone who is 'open to experience' according to the Five Factor Model. 
